<paragraph id="241878FF92F2F3EAD532100DC6C1F390" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B6BB084B508525FF177F4CFAAF57F98" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="2E0EDEC8E20BAAA8D904B3D10D39FC61" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum deflexicarpum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexicarpum">
<emphasis id="0F116FB99763129B276D9B66CA7D68E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum deflexicarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in open vegetation and roadsides in semideciduous tropical forests, from 1,255 to 1,500 m elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
